// GOOGLE DOCS ESTIMATION

// OPERATIONAL TRANSFORM QPS:
// Assume 40 WPM typing = 40 × 5 chars / 60 sec ≈ 3.3 chars/sec per user
// 50M DAU, peak: 50% using app = 25M users
// Of those, 30% actively typing = 7.5M typing simultaneously
// OT operations/sec = 7.5M × 3.3 ≈ 25M ops/sec (average)
// Peak = 25M × 3 = 75M ops/sec
// Each operation: {docId, userId, position, char, timestamp} ≈ 100 bytes
// → 75M × 100 bytes = 7.5GB/sec of edit operations!
// Solution: in-memory processing per document server
//           only persist to DB periodically (every 5 seconds)

// DOCUMENT STORAGE:
// Active documents: 50M DAU × 3 docs = 150M document edits/day
// Store diffs (not full doc per edit): avg diff = 100 bytes
// Daily diffs: 150M × 100 bytes = 15GB/day (manageable)
// Full snapshot every hour: 50M docs × 50KB = 2.5TB (hot storage)
// Old versions (archive): 2.5TB grows 2.5TB/day → object storage (S3)

// WEBSOCKET CONNECTIONS:
// 50M DAU, 30% online at peak = 15M concurrent connections
// Each connection server: 100K connections
// Connection servers = 15M / 100K = 150 servers

// LATENCY CONSTRAINT:
// Target: < 100ms round trip for edit to appear to collaborators
// Network: client-to-server ≈ 30ms (CDN/regional servers)
// OT processing: < 5ms (in-memory, extremely fast)
// Server-to-collaborator push: 30ms
// Total: ~65ms ✓

// ARCHITECTURE:
// Key insight: all editors of ONE document MUST go to SAME server
// Otherwise: OT conflict resolution is distributed problem
// Solution: document-to-server mapping in Redis
// hash(docId) → server_id
// Load balancer reads this mapping → routes all docId=X to server-3

// DOCUMENT SERVER:
class DocumentServer {
    // In-memory state per active document
    Map<String, DocumentState> activeDocuments;

    void handleEdit(String docId, Operation op, String userId) {
        DocumentState state = activeDocuments.get(docId);

        // Apply Operational Transform (resolve conflict if concurrent edits)
        Operation transformed = state.transform(op);
        state.apply(transformed);

        // Broadcast to all connected editors of this doc
        state.getCollaborators().forEach(collaborator ->
            webSocket.push(collaborator, transformed)
        );

        // Async: persist to database every 5 seconds
        // Not on every keystroke — too slow!
    }
}

